
<% priority 10 %>

<% if details['num'] >1 %>
<% name "Strict MIME Type [#{details['num']} urls]" %>
<% else %>
<% name "Strict MIME Type [1 url]" %>
<% end %>

<b>Description:</b> MIME type mismatch found or nosniff header missed. Some browsers will automatically switch to using an interpreter for the real content type. This increases exposure to XSS attack.<br/>


<%= "<b>Affected URLs:</b><br/>" %>

<% details['list'].each do |endpoint| %>
	
	<%= "#{endpoint['url']}<br/>" %>
<% end %>

<b>Advice: </b> Use response header X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff to prevent MIME sniffing or make sure MIME type mismatch not exist.<br/>
